This paper deals with the control of robot orientation, which is a core problem in robotics. The use of unit quaternions to represent orientations is a common technique in robotics, and the paper focuses on designing a control system for dynamical movement primitives (DMPs) in Cartesian space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. 

The paper also deals with the design of a control system, which implies a focus on control theory. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. 

The paper uses unit quaternions to represent orientations, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and computer vision. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
